mages/broodwar/popup/corsair.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How do YOU use CH?</span><hr size=1> Seeing as how we clerics are solitary folk, and we rarely get to group with our own kind, I thought it would be interesting to find out how you all use CH.  I’ve noticed that even in the upper 40’s, people get nervous when I wait until they are at 2 bubs of health before starting CH, even though I never let them die.  This would suggest that the other clerics they’ve been playing with (you guys) are doing something different.  <br>
<br>
I personally use CH as much as possible, since it’s hands down our most mana efficient heal, as long as you are healing 961 hit points or more.  As a result, I've got a reputation among my friends for never ever being OOM (the enchanter usually runs out first <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  Anyone else have input on this? <p><img src=http://www.ispwest.com/gtath1.jpg>
<br>
Cleric of the 47th Prayer</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugtath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gtath</A> at: 12/7/00 9:27:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udollie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dollie</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/dollie_one/celicon.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/7/00 12:58:47 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/dollie_one/pic1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU use CH?</span><hr size=1> It all depend of the situation, usually when my tanks are on 1 mob and got situation in hand i wait till 1 and a half bub, sometimes 1, dont want to take any chances but never loose folks :)<br>
<br>
if hp's are dropping fast i start healing at 2 bubs of life, with a tank over 2500 hp's, 2/5 of is hp's is enough to get him in time.<br>
<br>
Im never oom neither except when there are 6 monsters and cant get mez'ed fast enough wich usually never happen :) <p><b>
