Cleric of the 47th Prayer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udrabcounterpoint.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drab Counterpoint</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.csh.rit.edu/~marius/eq/bored/brane.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/9/00 11:50:42 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.csh.rit.edu/~marius/eq/bored/drab.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU use CH?</span><hr size=1> I use up a CH rather quickly with the following methods:<br>
1) I do multi-mob crowd control on anything higher than a low blue.<br>
2) Breaking charm on a FG.<br>
3) Giving the clerics mana during a pull.<br>
4) Out-damaging all the tanks.<br>
5) When mez breaks and I've been using mana song the whole time during a 45 minute battle.<br>
 <p><hr><br>
Drab Counterpoint<br>
/guildleader Lore Keepers<br>
51st Minstrel lost and confused<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uisyssreigns.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Isyss Reigns</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/11/00 7:07:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU use CH?</span><hr size=1> CHeal has to be used with exact amount of time estimated depending on the mob the tank fighting or how many, if health drops fast, forget CHeal, your tank is dead. But i understand what you're saying Gtath, most players gets nervous and in turn &quot;tells you&quot; what to do and when to heal. Cheal casting should start at 2 bubs left for the tank. <br>
<br>
Unless I'm bored, and moving reeaaally slow...and have been FM for awhile now, maybe once in awhile i'll use Sheal. I have to do something before I fall asleep on my Keyboard /grin.<br>
<br>
