 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uperplexcerebrum.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Perplex Cerebrum</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/cortexcerebrum/perplex_dot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/14/00 6:05:44 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/cortexcerebrum/perplex_photo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU use CH?</span><hr size=1> Depends on who the tank is, the level and class, as well as the type of mob that is beating on him. Level 49 Ranger maleeing a tough mob is quite a different story from a level 49 warrior maleeing a moderate one, even when appropriatelly buffed. Its a matter of damage rate, which of course depends on HP, AC and monster damage. Sometimes you can wait till 1.5 bubbles to start casting, other times you may have to start at half HP or the tank is going to go into the purple haze. I usually start of on the safe side and lower the threshold as I get more comfortable with the situation. <p><br>
<img src="http://www.geocities.com/cortexcerebrum/perplex_sig.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udonord.showPublicProfile?language=EN>donord</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/14/00 7:30:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU use CH?</span><hr size=1> CHeal also makes a nice taunt for when you wanna start the summoning cycle.  <br>
