you have been slain by froglok illis shaman<br>
LOADING, PLEASE WAIT... <p>Donord<br>
Level 53 DORF cleric of Brell<br>
Proud member of Rune of Flame</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubandamerstormrider.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bandamer Stormrider</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/18/00 11:59:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU use CH?</span><hr size=1> On warriors and pallies I start at 2 bubs of life.  However, that is talking normal group - fighting one mob and enchanter having others mezzed.  In muli mob fights - say 2(no chanters present) I start at half life &amp; have a message that says cheal inc on so and so..etc...i'm out 10 seconds.  Before when I didn't have that little social key in there I'd have tanks asking - you gonna heal? hehe quite amusing it was.  In Hate and Fear I have never used CH once during a fight that I recall.  There are too many variables that can happen.  Maybe I'm just not comfortable yet - but if a wiz or someone gets lagged and summoned - I must be able to switch and heal them.  That's my 2 cents - I use sup and celestial heal in planes mostly.<br>
<br>
Bandamer (The Viking) Stormrider<br>
49th Seasoning Dorfy Cleric of TCC<br>
&amp; Honorary 1st Lt of The Viking Squad, of General Caex's Assling Corps <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukaedian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaedian</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/cowboy_fan66/smallskull.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/22/00 7:21:32 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/cowboy_fan66/Kaed.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU use CH?</span><hr size=1> The trick is practicing on different mobs with a tank that trusts you completely.  Right Celest? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href=http://www.silentavengers.net><IMG
SRC=http://www.geocities.com/cowboy_fan66/kaedian1.jpg></a><br>
50th Skull -  Get a life?  Nah, I'll take yours instead.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uemillanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Emil Lanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/29/00 9:13:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do YOU use CH?</span><hr size=1> <br>
1) Are you leting the tank know you are using CH?  Informing them will help removing any concerns they may have. <br>
<br>
2) Ch timing has to be adjusted based on the tank and the mob hitting them. <br>
<br>
3) I always use remedy or divine light if we got mutiple mobs incomming *until* the environment(other mobs) are controlled. If your ching and your chanter dies because you cant heal them, that sucks. Same thing if you are ching and your tank dies. I use and cast CH only when we are fighting one mob at a time.  You need to learn how much your &quot;group tanks&quot; can take. Alot of level 57-60 tanks for example you can wait till 1 1/2 or even 1 bub before ching. While some 48-52 tanks you may need to start casting at 2 1/2 bubs to get off ch when they go between 0 and 1 bub left of life.<br>
<br>
